Title: DIESEL FORD E350 HITOP HANDICAPPED WHEELCHAIR LIFT MOBILITY VAN
Body: BURGUNDY MOBILITY VAN 2004 FORD  E350 HIGHTOP DIESEL 6.0 LITER

You are looking at a very nice Powerstroke Diesel 6.0 liter 2004 Ford E350 raised-roof raised-doors, power doors, handicap lift equipped van with a driver's 6-way power transfer seat. The van has 143,649 well cared for miles on it. This is a southern van that is ready to go anywhere and be used. THIS IS NOT YOUR AVERAGE "IT'S PERFECT CRAIGSLIST VAN. It has been inspected and serviced by 2 different mechanics, a front-end shop and a mobility technician. PLEASE LOOK AT THE LONG LIST OF NEW PARTS AND SERVICES THIS VAN HAS HAD DONE IN THE LAST FEW YEARS! We are happy to give you a copy of the Carfax report for free or you can click on the Carfax Emblem on our website ( WWW.NTSMOBILITYVANS.COM ) and see it now. The paint is very nice and very shiny and bright (van was completely repainted about 2 years ago). The body is very straight. You will have to hunt to even find a "door ding" on this van. The interior shows very little wear at all.  There are no holes or tears in the cloth seats, non-slip flooring or carpet. It has NOT been smoked in. JUST LOOK AT THE PICTURES OF HOW NICE THIS VAN IS. This van is mechanically very solid and cosmetically way better than average.  The previous owner spent a huge amount of money on this van in the last 15,000 miles and 2 1/2 years.  That they passed away, is the only reason the van is available.  We sold this van about 3 months and 4k miles ago.  They realized that the person in the wheelchair was not able to use a lift and traded it in on a minivan with a ramp.  We completely went over the van again for the 3rd time.
The van comes with the following options and conversion parts:
Seating for Driver + 1 Wheelchair + 7 Seated Passengers
The van also has the following mobility equipment and conversions:
Hand-Held Remote Control for Doors & Lift
Magnetic Switches in Tail Light for Doors/Lift
PLEASE NOTE: WE HAVE RECEIPTS WHERE THE MAIN HYDRAULIC CYLINDER FOR THE RAMP ALONG WITH THE BARRIER ROLL STOP ACTUATOR, WHERE JUST REPLACED.   THIS LIFT WORKS PERFECTLY.

The van was inspected and serviced by my mechanics and a front-end shop.  We also have a huge amount of receipts for work the previous owner had done in the last few years.  PLEASE NOTE: MOST ALL OF THESE REPAIRS/SERVICES ARE REPORTED ON THE CARFAX.  You will see 53 service history records on the Carfax for this van.
I have receipts for the following having been done in the last 2 1/2 years:
New High Pressure Fuel Pump/Oil Pump
You will see they addressed all the issues that the 6.0 liter had when they first came out.   This van is rock solid and runs great.

THIS IS NOT YOUR AVERAGE CRAIGSLIST VAN. Come look at it and see for yourself.  It has been gone over by 4 different people to make sure everything is right. It has NO leaks or drips. It does not smoke. The transmission shifts out solidly and smoothly. There are no wobbles or shakes at 70 mph on the freeway. The tires are 80% to brand new. The van is 100% ready to be driven anywhere and be enjoyed.

We are a licensed Texas auto dealer located in Irving, Texas. We specialize in affordable handicap vans. We always have 5-10 vans that are in the process of being serviced and ready for sale. So if this van doesn't quite fit your needs, give me a call. I may have just what you are looking for in my warehouse. 80% of my vans are sold before they are even ready, so feel free to contact me. We do accept trade-ins and we do have financing available for those with good credit. We can take an application and get you pre-approved as well. WE ARE ALSO ALWAYS ON THE LOOK-OUT FOR GOOD HANDICAP VANS TO PURCHASE, SO FEEL FREE TO CONTACT US IF YOU HAVE ONE FOR SALE.

You are looking at a very nice 2009 Ford E150 XLT lowered-floor, removable seats, handicap lift equipped van with a NORCAL conversion. The van has 87,177 well cared for miles on it. There are no holes or tears in the cloth seats or carpet. It has NOT been smoked in. JUST LOOK AT THE PICTURES OF HOW NICE THIS VAN IS. This van is mechanically very solid and cosmetically way better than average. It has had the front chrome bumper replaced and the bottom edges of the 2 passenger's doors painted.

Seating For 6 Plus Driver Plus Wheelchair or 5 Plus Driver Plus 2 Wheelchairs

Lowered Floor from Rear Seat to Firewall

The van is 100% ready to be driven anywhere and be enjoyed.
